Entrezgene.Entrezgene_summary: Enables insulin binding activity and insulin-activated receptor activity. Involved in several processes, including gamete generation; lipid homeostasis; and positive regulation of cell development. Is integral component of plasma membrane. Part of insulin receptor complex. Is expressed in several structures, including central nervous system; corpus allatum; gastrula embryo; gut section; and posterior midgut primordium. Used to study alcohol dependence; high grade glioma; sleep disorder; and type 2 diabetes mellitus. Human ortholog(s) of this gene implicated in several diseases, including dementia (multiple); diabetes mellitus (multiple); kidney cancer (multiple); liver disease (multiple); and reproductive organ cancer (multiple). Orthologous to several human genes including IGF1R (insulin like growth factor 1 receptor). [provided by Alliance of Genome Resources, Apr 2022]
